# Privacy Policy

## Introduction and Overview

This Privacy Policy explains how data is handled on SteamInputDB in accordance with the General Data Protection Regulation (EU) 2016/679 and applicable European laws. The terms are gender-neutral.

We want to describe clearly what happens with any personal data that may be involved when using our website.  
Most of the time, we do not store personal data ourselves, except for user-generated content like comments.  

## Scope of Application

Users can create accounts only via third-party login through Steam.  
We do not operate our own registration system and do not maintain a database of personal user profiles beyond the information needed to associate user interactions with a Steam account.  
All other personal data, such as login credentials, remains with Steam and is subject to their privacy policy.

Third-party content, such as texts or images, may appear on the site, and we have no control over it.

## Legal Basis

The personal data we store (user comments, ratings, votes, and similar interactions) is processed under the legal basis of **legitimate interest (Article 6(1)(f) GDPR)**.  
This allows users to interact on the site, display contributions publicly, and maintain continuity of user interactions.

All other personal data, such as login credentials, remains with Steam and is subject to their privacy policy.  

## Contact

For questions regarding data protection, please see our [Imprint](/imprint).

## Data Storage

When you interact with SteamInputDB (by posting comments, giving ratings, votes, or similar actions) we store the content of your interaction and the Steam user ID associated with it.  
This allows the website to display your contributions and track interactions tied to your account.  

If we have stored any data you can completely delete it by visiting your profile page and deleting your account.

We do not store passwords, email addresses, or any other personal information from Steam. All other personal data is processed and stored only by the third-party services.

## Security

SteamInputDB is hosted in Europe. The website uses HTTPS to ensure secure communication.  
We take reasonable steps to protect the server and the website, but we do not track or store additional personal data ourselves.

## Cookies

Cookies may be set only for basic website functionality or by third-party services.  
We do not use cookies for tracking or profiling.  
You can manage or delete cookies through your browser settings at any time.

## Third-Party Content

The website may display content from third parties, such as images or text.  
We do not control these materials and cannot be responsible for any data collection or processing by the third parties.

## User Rights

If personal data is processed (for example, comments associated with a Steam ID), you have rights under the GDPR.  
You may request access, correction, or deletion of your stored comments.  
To exercise these rights, please contact us.  

Data processed by third parties, such as your Steam account information, is governed by the privacy policies of those services.

## Final Notes

We are committed to transparency and explaining how data is handled on SteamInputDB.  
If you have questions about this Privacy Policy or about data processed via third-party services, please contact us.
